column5: To say the least,the ice is going away very fast and if your are foolish enough to go out there,then you deserve what you get.          As for the spring and mates Thier starting to pair up. Love is in the air.          These teo poor fellas are still looking.       I found a friend that wanted to play peek a boo on the tree.LOL    I finally tagged him out.
I'll be out there in the boat as soon as I can.  Thanks for the primer.
Really enjoying that new camera eh B  Nice pics, hope nobody is dumb enough to go out there.  Joey
One quick dip in that freezing water would put all thoughts of romance out of my mind.  JF

Well Believe it or not Brian, I saw two guys out in the middle of Little Lake this afternoon. I tell ya no fish is worth anybody's life. Stay off the ice around here anyways, people!  Rob

Hit the cottage on Rice Lake this afternoon to take in the awsome weather. Here are some shots. The temperature was 15 C and the lake was like glass, not a wave around. The bottom of lake was quite visible. Water is quite clear. Can't wait to start the fishing season. As you can see the ice already gone. The view today from Thunder Bay to the Sleeping Giant shows lots ice ice still, until you run into the areas that the ice breakers have cleaned up. I wouldn't be caught dead on Superior at this time of year, but there's still well over a month of ice action on the inland lakes up here. Be careful out there guys. Common sense goes a long way.
